The paper proposes a novel approach for video-based person re-identification using convolutional neural network (CNN) and recurrent neural network (RNN) to extract spatial and temporal features. The focus is on splitting the human body into parts to obtain more specific features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for feature extraction and representation suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of video data and the focus on temporal features could also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves the development of a Siamese network, which is a type of neural network used for similarity learning, suggesting that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks for temporal modeling could also suggest the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
